<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="530" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,438,895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,331,798,823]" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Etymology</emphasis>
Name formed by combining the suffix 
<emphasis box="[808,888,798,823]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Berber</emphasis>
(pertaining to the Maghrebian Roman region, Barbaria, and the prevailing ethnic group in northern Maghreb) and the prefix –getta, an arbitrary combination of letters associated with small cicada species, as in 
<taxonomicName box="[751,859,871,894]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Tettigetta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[751,859,871,894]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="530">Tettigetta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
